# Repository Configuration

## .gitattributes

The .gitattributes file provides a way of configuring how git performs actions on the repo.

https://git-scm.com/docs/gitattributes

### Line Endings

The line endings of specific file types can be set.
For example to ensure git uses *lf* line endings for *.sh* files the following could be put in the .gitignore:
```
*.sh    text eol=lf
```

